question: New Zealand Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern, who won a second term, belongs to which party?
explanation:
New Zealand Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern has won a landslide victory in the country's general election.
Jacinda Ardern belongs to the Labour Party, which won 49.1% in the election to bring an estimated 64 seats and a complete parliamentary majority. The opposition centre-right National Party won 26.8% in the poll with 35 seats.
